# === Third-party reference material (LOCAL ONLY — never commit) ===
# Folders under assets/ containing third-party copyrighted material used
# strictly as local visual/audio reference during pre-production. All
# placeholder and ship art is authored under assets/art/, assets/audio/,
# etc. — never sourced from these folders.
#
# Canonical English directory names (after tools/rename-octopath-dirs.py):
assets/octopath*/
assets/_reference/
# Belt-and-suspenders: catch a future re-drop that still has the Chinese
# names before the rename tool is run. 八方旅人 = "Octopath Traveler".
assets/八方旅人*/
# Assembled demo assets (produced by tools/demo-asset-setup.py from above
# sources; local only — never commit placeholder derivative assets).
assets/art/demo/
assets/audio/demo/
# tools/demo-asset-setup.py ALSO writes placeholder hero art to the production
# paths the game references (HeroClass.tres sprite_path/portrait_path =
# assets/art/classes/<id>/{sprite,portrait}.png), plus Godot's .import sidecars.
# These are demo-phase IP placeholders — ignored so a stray `git add -A` can
# never commit Square Enix art. When ORIGINAL production art is authored to
# these paths, delete this line (and the .import files become committable normally).
assets/art/classes/
# Same for per-enemy demo sprites (EnemyData.sprite_path =
# assets/art/enemies/<id>/sprite.png), assembled from the Octopath enemy archive.
assets/art/enemies/

# === Marrow (eval tooling — never commit, upstream framework v1.0) ===
marrow/

# === Runtime Artifacts (auto-generated, start empty on fresh clone) ===
# Created on first use by /consistency-check and /architecture-review
docs/consistency-failures.md

# GdUnit4 HTML/XML test reports (regenerated on every test run)
reports/

# GdUnit4 test-run fixture subdirs (regenerated per test; only the canonical
# helper files under tests/fixtures/data_registry/ belong in git)
tests/fixtures/data_registry/*/

