credentials.json
secrets.json
# Asset-pipeline API keys (ElevenLabs / Gemini). The .example template IS
# committed; the real keys.env is NEVER committed.
# NOTE: ignore the directory *contents* (`.secrets/*`), NOT the directory
# (`.secrets/`) — git will not descend into an ignored directory, so a bare
# `.secrets/` rule makes the negation below dead and keys.env.example
# uncommittable. `.secrets/*` lets git descend so the `!` re-includes the template.
.secrets/*
!.secrets/*.example

